SST and Chl-a Regional Summaries

February 01, 2022

Below are monthly time series of mean sea surface temperature (SST, \(^\circ\)C) and chlorophyll-a concentration (Chla, mg m-3) for regions and stations of interest, including Marine Protected Areas. Click on the tabs to view plots.

The SST is a 4km resolution product available from NOAA, covering late 1981 to present. The Chla is a 4km product available from the NASA Ocean Biology Processing Group covering 2003 to present.

Note that these plots are current to July, 2021.

The time series are coloured by season: winter (January, February, March), spring (April, May, June), summer (July, August, September), and autumn (October, November, December).

Click here to view map



Oceanographic Regions (orange boundary):

  • AOI: Offshore Pacific Area of Interest
  • EHV: Endeavour Hydrothermal Vents Marine Protected Area
  • GH: East (GHE), Offshore (GHO), South (GHS), West (GHW) Gwaii Haanas National Marine Conservation Area Reserve
  • SI: Scott Islands marine National Wildlife Area
  • SK-B: SGaan Kinghlas-Bowie Seamount Marine Protected Area
  • SR: Central (SRC), North (SRN), South (SRS) Hecate Strait/Queen Charlotte Sound Glass Sponge Reefs Marine Protected Area

Selected standard oceanographic stations used for further calculations are shown as yellow points (stations GI02, Mason53, P4). The statistics used are from a 5x5 pixel box centered at the station coordinates.

Climatology Plots

The monthly climatological mean is indicated by a grey line, with shading at 25 and 75 percentiles, and dashed lines indicating upper and lower standard deviation from the mean. All regions are displayed on the same scale.

The progress of 2021 is shown as the black line with points coloured according to season.
